description: Write clear, simple, maintainable CSS/UX/UI code without duplication
alwaysApply: true
---

CSS/UX/UI code must follow best practices:
- Write clear, simple, and easily maintainable code
- Avoid code duplication - extract repeated elements into variables
- Use CSS custom properties for consistent theming
- Follow BEM methodology or similar naming conventions
- Keep CSS specificity low and avoid !important
- Use semantic HTML and accessible design patterns
- Optimize for performance and maintainability
- Document complex CSS logic and design decisions
